This does look like some kind of race condition.  The `TextInput.show` platform message sent by the framework is reaching the Android embedding.  But in profile mode the call to `TextInputPlugin.showTextInput` will happen at a slightly earlier point in the embedding's lifecycle and the keyboard will not be displayed.

I noticed that `InputMethodManager.isActive(view)` was returning false when the keyboard does not show.  Adding this to `TextInputPlugin.showTextInput` appears to work:

```
    if (mImm.isActive(view)) {
      mImm.showSoftInput(view, 0);
    } else {
      view.post(new Runnable() {
        public void run() {
          mImm.showSoftInput(view, 0);
        }
      });
    }
```

Not sure if there is a better solution.

